          "CRITIQUE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction of M0850003 could be interpreted as",
                " 181Ta(g,n)180Ta, but not as 181Ta(g,n0)180Ta-g."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma-quanta energy spectrum lines data.",
                "For adaptation of the experimental spectra the",
                " Winspectrum program was used. This program permits",
                " the user to process the spectra in definite time",
                " controls, therefore, enabling the identification of",
                " the nuclides from the energies of the g-rays and",
                " their half-lives.",
                "To obtain the population for the isomeric state with",
                " IPi = 8- for the 181Ta(g,p)180Hf-m reaction at",
                " Eg-max = 20 MeV the net peak area of 215.3 keV g-rays",
                " which depopulated the excited level of 180Hf-m was",
                " measured.",
                "To get the population of 180Hf-m at Eg-max = 40 and",
                " 55 MeV the photo-peak activity of 443.1 keV g-rays",
                " were determined."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the first time the flux-weighted average yields",
                " of 180Hf-m in (g,p) reaction were measured by",
                " activation and off-line g-ray spectrometric",
                " technique at the bremsstrahlung end-point energies",
                " of 20, 40 and 55 MeV.",
                "Using weighted-average fluxes of bremsstrahlung",
                " gamma-rays the weighted-average reaction cross",
                " sections could be obtained and therefore only",
                " integrated cross sections are in fact measured in",
                " experiments."
              ]
            }
          ],
